dct_title_s: Vilayet de Brousse ou de Hudavendighiar : divisé en 5 sandjaks, 28 cazas renfermant 44 nahiés  / par Vital Cuinet ; éditieur Ernest Leroux.
dct_description_sm: Prime meridian is centered in Paris. Map shows administrative boundaries (vilayet, sandjaks, cazas), railroads,  projected railroads, roads; roads in construction, paths, and forests. Vilayet de Brousse ou de Hudavendighiar  was a first level adminisrative division vilayet  [province] of the Ottoman Empire. Covers five Sandjaks [departments]: 1. Brousse  -- 2. d'Erthogroul -- 3. Kutahia-- 4. Kara - Hissar-- 5.Karassi. On left margin of map: Mutessariflik d'Ismidt : 5 cazas, contenant 13 nahiés: Cazas:1. Ismid -- 2.Ada-Bazar -- 3. Gueïvé -- 4. Kara-mursal --5. Kandra. Original map is filed in the Map/Geospatial Center, a map reproduction is attached to companion volume.
